Values for vapour thermal conductivity coefficient (


                                 λ


                                 v


                        ), the vapour dynamic viscosity coefficient (


                                 μ


                                 v


                        ), and the vapour binary diffusion coefficient (


                                 D


                                 ab


                        ) listed in Table 1 for the electrolyte solvents used in this work are currently not available in literature due to lack of documentation. For these reasons, most of the values for the listed characteristics were estimated by using the theoretical and empirical correlations listed in 
                        Table 2. To assess their reliability, a comparison between their predicted values under given conditions and experimental data of IPA reported in the literature was performed. All parameters were predicted with an error below 10 %, with the highest error for vapour thermal conductivity. Correlations for the diffusion coefficient are obtained from a linear regression estimated with the equation in Table 2. Vapour thermal conductivity were estimated with Chung et al (
                        Poling et al., 2020
                        ). empirical correlations for all considered compounds (See Table 2). The vapour dynamic viscosity coefficient for IPA was found in literature (Perry and Green, 2008), while for DMC and DEC the Chung et al. correlation was used. The binary diffusion coefficient for IPA and DEC was also estimated through the Chung et al. correlation, while their experimental vapour pressure values were found in literature, and are reporter as semi-empirical Antoine equations in Table 1.
